programme.title: Encouraged
programme.sub-title: Courage Adams returns home to Nigeria
programme.desc: At age 16 Courage Adams turned pro, taking the BMX world by storm. Now, he returns to his roots in Nigeria. At age 12 Courage Adams started riding BMX, but by age 16 he'd turned pro, taken the BMX world by storm and made the most of his parents' bold move. Now, he returns to his roots in Nigeria.

programme.title: The Flare
programme.sub-title: Finding their own place in skateboarding
programme.desc: Take a whimsical look at the life of skateboarding with a group of young men just trying to not fit in. A jock, an outcast, a rebel and a princess: this modern-day Breakfast Club tell their story a little differently. Take a whimsical look at the life of skateboarding with a group of young men just trying to not fit in.

programme.title: Digging deep
programme.desc: Josh Kerr is looking to boost results while Taj Burrow digs deep to go after the elusive world title. Following a consistent run of top 10 finishes, Josh Kerr is looking to boost results in the 2014 season and prove his worth as a top contender. Meanwhile, Taj Burrow digs deep for motivation to go after the elusive world title.

programme.title: Episode 26
programme.desc: Taj Burrow and Josh Kerr are less than two weeks away from competing in the second contest of the 2014 tour. Taj Burrow and Josh Kerr are less than two weeks away from competing in the second contest of the 2014 World Tour. Burrow fine tunes his preparations in his hometown, while Kerr works to balance family and surfing.

programme.title: Marol
programme.desc: From a small area in Mumbai called Marol comes some of the city's richest hip-hop culture. From a small area in Mumbai called Marol comes some of the city's richest hip-hop culture. Get to know the locals and how they have seen the culture of hip-hop transform the growing city.

programme.title: The secret fan in Argentina
programme.desc: Argentinian football fan Diego Milner gives a camouflage lesson in how to infiltrate a rival team's area. Argentinian Diego Milner is on a waiting list to be an official supporter of his beloved team, Boca Juniors. Until then, he has to infiltrate a rival team's area. Here he gives a lesson in camouflage.

programme.title: In Chile you'll never play alone
programme.desc: Sebastian Carrera has travelled more than one-and-a-half turns around the Earth to accompany his team. Sebastian Carrera has travelled more than one-and-a-half turns around the Earth to accompany his team, Deportes Puerto Montt, in the extreme south of Chile.

programme.title: Chennai
programme.desc: Here’s a look at how Chennai’s hip-hop scene is heavily inspired by one locality – Vyasarpadi. Here’s a look at how Chennai’s hip-hop scene is heavily inspired by one locality – Vyasarpadi. In an Indian city literally built of oppression locals are finding a home for their creativity.

programme.title: Brazil's devoted fandom
programme.desc: Lorena Amaro is such a devout fan, even her cat is black and white in honour of her favourite team. Lorena Amaro is such a devout fan, even her cat is black and white in honour of Atlético Mineiro, her favourite team.

programme.title: Giving it everything
programme.desc: Italian skier Dominik Paris seeks the Super-G title of the men's tour in Andorra. Italian skier Dominik Paris, who started competing in skiing at the age of six, seeks the Super-G title of the men's tour in Andorra. Paris is hoping that his victory will end the seven-season winning streak of his Norwegian competitors.

programme.title: Lindsey Vonn says goodbye
programme.desc: As Lindsey Vonn retires, Sofia Goggia and Viktoria Rebensburg leave their mark on the 2019 ski season. Lindsey Vonn bids farewell to a storybook skiing career in Soldeu, Andorra, as Sofia Goggia and Viktoria Rebensburg make their final marks on the 2019 World Cup season.

programme.title: Playrooms
programme.sub-title: Exploring the Future of Club Culture
programme.desc: A futuristic look at the use of technology to unlock the sixth sense and change the club experience forever. Embark on an odyssey into a futuristic experiment of sensory stimulation in club culture. How can the evolution of technology unlock the sixth sense and provide the ultimate club experience? It's time to party like it's 2099.

programme.title: The gathering place
programme.desc: Get an inside look at the people living in Volcom's two houses at Pipeline on Oahu's North Shore, Hawaii. Get an inside look into the two Volcom Houses in Hawaii, and the group of surfers living there for the winter. Carlos Muñoz takes us to the Dungeon, Dusty Payne defends his title at the Hawaiian Pro, and the group paddles out for a fallen friend.

programme.title: Turkey day
programme.desc: Surfers at the Volcom houses on Oahu's North Shore, Hawaii prepare for Thanksgiving and the Vans World Cup. The Volcom houses get ready for Thanksgiving. Tai Vandyke cooks his 18th annual feast for the team, Mitch Coleborn trains for the Vans World Cup, and a pair of vets and groms share their takes on what surfing in Hawaii means to them.

programme.title: Contest day
programme.desc: The Volcom Pipe Pro arrives and all of Volcom's big names and dark horses are looking to make their mark. The Vans World Cup of surfing begins. All of Volcom's big names are on Hawaii’s North Shore and looking to make their mark. Elsewhere, one of the team's most iconic surfers turns up at the Volcom house, as does a rising star from Brazil.​.

programme.title: The Broken Collarbone
programme.desc: When it comes to injuries, there's one club every pro downhill rider belongs to: the snapped collarbone. Broken collarbones go with downhill mountain biking like tree roots and tyre size debates. The athletes and the professionals who treat their injuries weigh in on the most common injury in the sport and how to recover from it.

programme.title: The Trunk
programme.desc: Athletes and doctors struggle with the protection and rehab of one of the body's most vulnerable sections. For a downhill mountain biker, protection is a balancing act. Too much can hamper performance, but too little can mean injuries that end seasons, or worse. This is no truer than with the athlete's trunk, which is vulnerable, yet difficult to protect.

programme.title: The Head
programme.desc: Top MTB riders explain how they balance the risk of head injuries with the desire to go faster at all costs. Despite mountain biking helmets being safer than ever before, head injuries still occur and can have serious neurological consequences. So how do you reduce the risk after multiple crashes? Top riders, including Gee Atherton, explain.
